criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  women of reproductive age (20-44 years);

          -  native Minangkabau ethnic (both father and mother from the Minangkabau tribe);

          -  had abnormal one of isolated blood lipid profiles (cholesterol > 200 mg / dl,
             LDL-cholesterol >100 mg / dl, HDL < 60 mg/dl, TG > 150 mg/dl);

          -  signing a written inform consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  in pregnancy;

          -  having a history or active smoker and alcoholic addict;

          -  has a history of heart disease, diabetes, asthma, cancer, chronic digestive tract
             disorders, hemophilia and other chronic diseases;

          -  routinely taking cholesterol-lowering or blood pressure medications;

          -  vegetarians;

          -  use estrogen therapy;

          -  are participating in other studies.
